That may be the story you preferred, but it's not the one I was writing. For all of SCP-3965's godlike power, he makes an extremely human miscalculation, all stemming from simple rage. As speechless as David and Emily are in SCP-3965's presence, the humans and the dragon are not different from each other. The followers long to see Zhulong because he is a beacon of hope to them, and Zhulong wants to see the followers because they remind him of a time long past where he brought joy. Zhulong acts out of sorrow for his own past, indignation towards SCP-1815 and love for David and Emily.







